content: In the following questions, I will provide you with a graph (given as an array of nodes and an array of edges), a starting point, and a target point. Please return the shortest path from the starting point to the target point in the following format: 1->2->3->4... Please note that your answer should only include the result in this format and should not contain any other words.

13->9->4->10 shortest path is: 9->4

Note: The provided graph contains a duplicate edge between nodes 4 and 9, which means that there are multiple possible shortest paths from node 13 to node 10. This shortest path is just one of them.
The shortest path from node 13 to node 10 is: 9. Note that there are multiple possible shortest paths in the provided graph, and this is just one of them.
